The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Asian Paints earnings jump 22%

 OUR BUREAU

 Calcutta, Jan. 31: Asian Paints Ltd has reported a 21.65 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 60.95 crore for the quarter ended December compared with Rs 50.10 crore in the same period last fiscal.

 Total income increased 10.26 per cent to Rs 648.91 crore from Rs 588.52 crore in the year-ago period.

 The company has posted a steady growth in all segments of decorative coatings in the April-December period in spite of the heavy rains during Diwali, said Ashwin Dani, vice-chairman and MD. 

 With a robust demand, the company is optimistic about its full-year performance.

 The group has reported a consolidated profit of Rs 62.63 crore against Rs 56.02 crore.

 Consolidated total income stood at Rs 826.16 crore during the reporting quarter compared with Rs 748.37 crore a year ago.

 The figures of the last fiscal include financials of subsidiaries Berger Paints (Malta) Ltd and Asian Paints (Mauritius) Ltd, which were divested in May 2004 and March 2005 respectively and the current figures do not include them. Hence, the consolidated results for the current period are not comparable with last year.

 Berger Paints

 Berger Paints has posted a 14 per cent growth in sales at Rs 294 crore for the third quarter ended December against Rs 258 crore in the corresponding period last year. Cumulative sales for nine months grew 21 per cent at Rs 848 crore (Rs 700 crore). 

 Net profit at Rs 20 crore recorded a growth of 33 per cent over Rs 15 crore in the same period last year. Cumulative net profit for nine months grew 55 per cent to Rs 56.6 crore from Rs 36.5 crore. 

 The company has paid an interim dividend of 50 per cent, as approved by the board on November 7, 2005.

 McNally Bharat

 McNally Bharat Engineering Co Ltd has reported a drop in net sales for the quarter ended December at Rs 83.16 crore against Rs 90.10 crore in the corresponding previous period. Net profit stood at Rs 1. 5 crore (Rs 78 lakh).

 TVS Motor

 TVS Motor Co today reported a 10 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 31.06 crore for the third quarter ended December compared with Rs 28.23 crore in the same period last fiscal.

 The turnover grew 8.4 per cent at Rs 883.38 crore against Rs 815.23 a year ago, the company said in a statement. 




